      <h1 class='title'>POWER TO EXCLUDE SERVICES FROM EFFECT OF SECTION 8</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='grand-committee-report-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 27 June 2000 vol 614 cc7-8GC</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_7gc' title='Col. 7GC &mdash; HL Deb 27 June 2000 vol 614 c7GC' name='column_7gc' href='#column_7gc' rel='bookmark'>7GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0614P0-03586'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0614P0_20000627_GCR_44' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (" .&#x2014;(1) If a notice given by the CAA to a licence holder so provides, such air traffic services as are specified in the notice are to be treated as not being authorised services for the purposes of section 8 in its application to that holder.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0614P0-03587'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0614P0_20000627_GCR_45' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (2) A notice under subsection (1) may specify the air traffic services by reference to part of a licensed area.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0614P0-03588'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0614P0_20000627_GCR_46' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (3) A notice under this section may be modified or revoked by a further notice given by the CAA to the holder concerned.").
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0614P0-03589'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0614P0_20000627_GCR_47' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        On Question, amendment agreed to.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0614P0-03590'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0614P0_20000627_GCR_48' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Clauses 9 to 13 agreed to.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0614P0-03591'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0614P0_20000627_GCR_49' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Clause 14 <span class="italic">[Commission's power to give direction]:</span>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0614P0-03592'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0614P0_20000627_GCR_50' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="member">Lord Macdonald of Tradeston</span> moved Amendment No. 6:
        <q>Page 10, line 9, leave out ("concerned are not appropriate") and insert ("set out in the notice are not the modifications which are needed").</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0614P0-03593'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0614P0_20000627_GCR_51' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        On Question, amendment agreed to.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0614P0-03594'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0614P0_20000627_GCR_52' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Clause 14, as amended, agreed to.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0614P0-03595'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0614P0_20000627_GCR_53' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Clause 15 <span class="italic">[Position where Commission gives direction]:</span>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0614P0-03596'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0614P0_20000627_GCR_54' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="member">Lord Macdonald of Tradeston</span> moved Amendments Nos. 7 to 9:
        <q>Page 10, line 41, leave out ("may") and insert ("must").</q>
        <q>Page 11, line 1, leave out ("may") and insert ("must").</q>
        <q>Page 11, line 26, leave out from ("Commission") to end of line 27 and insert ("must&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) publish a notice in such manner as the Commission thinks appropriate for bringing the matters to which it relates to the attention of persons likely to be affected by the modifications, and</li>
        <li>(b) serve a copy of the notice on the licence holder, a copy on the Secretary of State and a copy on the CAA.</li>
        </ol></q>
        <q>(7) The notice under subsection (6) must&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) state that the modifications have been made,</li>
        <li>(b) set them out, and</li>
        <li>(c) set out the reasons for making them.").</li>
        </ol></q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0614P0-03597'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0614P0_20000627_GCR_55' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        On Questions, amendments agreed to.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0614P0-03598'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0614P0_20000627_GCR_56' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Clause 15, as amended, agreed to.
      </p>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_8gc' title='Col. 8GC &mdash; HL Deb 27 June 2000 vol 614 c8GC' name='column_8gc' href='#column_8gc' rel='bookmark'>8GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0614P0-03599'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0614P0_20000627_GCR_57' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="member">Lord Macdonald of Tradeston</span> moved Amendment No. 10:
        <q>After Clause 15, insert the following new clause&#x2014;</q>
      </p>
      <ol class='xoxo'>
        
      </ol>
      
